Description: Sherd of pottery open vessel, perhaps a plate; slight remains of a moulding on convex side, light groove at edge on convex side. Convex side reserved; concave side (and exterior of moulding) slipped white with two red bands framing dull glaze band; part of one possible ray to the centre; on convex side incised inscription.
Curator's comments: It would be easiest to take this as a floor or foot, but the moulding is an oddity.
